<h1 class="doc-page-title">Administration</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">Administrative features for managing users, system settings, and configuration in COMPASS.</p>

<div class="alert alert-warning">
    <p class="mb-0"><strong>Note:</strong> Administrative features are only available to users with the Administrator role.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="overview">Administration overview</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS administration features enable system administrators to:</p>

                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6">Manage users</h3>
                                <p class="small mb-0">Create, edit, and manage user accounts and permissions.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6">Configure settings</h3>
                                <p class="small mb-0">Manage lookup tables, risk types, risk tiers, and action sources.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6">Define metrics</h3>
                                <p class="small mb-0">Create and configure performance and enterprise metrics.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6">Manage objectives</h3>
                                <p class="small mb-0">Create and maintain strategic objectives for alignment.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="users">User management</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Accessing user management</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Users</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>View the list of all users in the system</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating users</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new user"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter user details:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Email:</strong> User's DfE email address (must be unique)</li>
                            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Full name of the user</li>
                            <li><strong>Role:</strong> Select "Administrator" or "Standard user"</li>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Whether the account is active</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the user</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Editing users</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Find the user in the users list</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Edit"</strong></li>
                    <li>Update user details as needed</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Save changes"</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User roles</h3>
                
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card border-danger">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Administrator</h4>
                                <p class="small"><strong>Full system access including:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small mb-0">
                                    <li>All standard user capabilities</li>
                                    <li>User management</li>
                                    <li>System settings configuration</li>
                                    <li>Lookup table management</li>
                                    <li>Metric definitions</li>
                                    <li>Strategic objectives management</li>
                                    <li>Functional standards management</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card border-primary">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Standard user</h4>
                                <p class="small"><strong>Core feature access including:</strong></p>
                                <ul class="small mb-0">
                                    <li>View all products and data</li>
                                    <li>Create and edit RAID items</li>
                                    <li>Submit performance metrics</li>
                                    <li>Conduct functional standards assessments</li>
                                    <li>View reports and dashboards</li>
                                    <li>Manage personal settings</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Deactivating users</h3>
                <p>To temporarily disable a user account without deleting it:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Edit the user</li>
                    <li>Uncheck the <strong>"Active"</strong> checkbox</li>
                    <li>Save changes</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="small text-muted">Inactive users cannot sign in but their historical data and associations are preserved.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="settings">System settings</h2>
                
                <p>System settings allow administrators to manage lookup tables and configuration values used throughout COMPASS.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Accessing settings</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Settings</strong></li>
                    <li>Use the settings sidebar to navigate between different setting types:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Risk types (13 standard types)</li>
                            <li>Risk tiers (5 governance levels)</li>
                            <li>Action sources (4 origin types)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risk types</h3>
                <p>Define the categories used to classify risks. Risks can be assigned multiple types simultaneously.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Managing risk types:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Risk types</strong></li>
                    <li>View existing risk types with their codes and active status</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new risk type"</strong> to add a type</li>
                    <li>Enter:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Code:</strong> Unique uppercase identifier (e.g., "STRATEGY", "TECHNOLOGY")</li>
                            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Display name (e.g., "Strategy risk", "Technology risk")</li>
                            <li><strong>Summary:</strong> Concise one-line description</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Full definition with examples and guidance</li>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Toggle whether this type appears in forms</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Standard risk types (13 categories):</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Strategy risk</li>
                    <li>Governance risk</li>
                    <li>Operations risk</li>
                    <li>Legal risk</li>
                    <li>Property risk</li>
                    <li>Financial risk</li>
                    <li>Commercial risk</li>
                    <li>People risk</li>
                    <li>Technology risk</li>
                    <li>Information risk</li>
                    <li>Security risk</li>
                    <li>Project/Programme risk</li>
                    <li>Reputational risk</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
                    <p class="mb-0"><strong>Deletion protection:</strong> Risk types cannot be deleted if any risks are currently assigned to them. Reassign risks to different types first, or deactivate the type to hide it from forms.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risk tiers</h3>
                <p>Define the governance levels at which risks are managed, from tactical project risks to strategic cross-government risks.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Managing risk tiers:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Risk tiers</strong></li>
                    <li>View existing risk tiers ordered by governance level</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new risk tier"</strong> to add a tier</li>
                    <li>Enter:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Code:</strong> Unique identifier (e.g., "PROJECT", "DEPARTMENT")</li>
                            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Tier name (e.g., "Project-level risk")</li>
                            <li><strong>Summary:</strong> Concise scope description</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Full definition with governance details and examples</li>
                            <li><strong>Sort order:</strong> Hierarchical position (1 = lowest, 5 = highest)</li>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Whether tier appears in dropdowns</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Standard risk tiers (5 governance levels):</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Project-level risk:</strong> Tactical risks within a discrete project or service (managed by delivery teams)</li>
                    <li><strong>Programme-level risk:</strong> Risks across a set of related projects (managed by programme boards)</li>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio-level risk:</strong> Risks across multiple programmes or business area (managed by portfolio directors)</li>
                    <li><strong>Department-level risk:</strong> Strategic risks across the entire department (managed by executive board)</li>
                    <li><strong>Cross-government / systemic risk:</strong> Risks across multiple departments (managed by Cabinet Office)</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
                    <p class="mb-0">Risk tiers determine the appropriate governance oversight and escalation path. Use the sort order to maintain hierarchical structure from project through to cross-government level.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Action sources</h3>
                <p>Define the origins of actions for better tracking, categorisation, and traceability.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Managing action sources:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Action sources</strong></li>
                    <li>View existing action sources with their codes and summaries</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new action source"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Code:</strong> Unique identifier (e.g., "RISK", "SERVICE_ASSESSMENT")</li>
                            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Display name (e.g., "Risk", "Service Assessment")</li>
                            <li><strong>Summary:</strong> Concise one-line description</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Full definition with context and examples</li>
                            <li><strong>Sort order:</strong> Display position in dropdowns</li>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Whether source appears in dropdowns</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Standard action sources:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk:</strong> Actions created to mitigate, treat, or manage a risk</li>
                    <li><strong>Issue:</strong> Actions created to resolve, workaround, or close an issue</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone:</strong> Actions created to deliver a milestone or track progress</li>
                    <li><strong>Service Assessment:</strong> Actions from service assessment reviews (may be created by external teams)</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Action sources support third-party integration. Actions with "Service Assessment" source can be created via API by external assessment platforms.</li>
                        <li>Editing or deleting settings that are already in use may affect existing data. Use caution when modifying active settings.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="user-settings">User settings</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">My settings</h3>
                <p>Users can configure personal preferences through the My settings page, accessed from the user menu in the top navigation bar.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Configuring preferences:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the <strong>user icon</strong> in the top navigation</li>
                    <li>Select <strong>My settings</strong> from the dropdown</li>
                    <li>Configure your preferences:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Preferred business areas:</strong> Select business areas to automatically filter RAID views</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Save preferences</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">How preferences work:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>RAID index pages automatically filter to your preferred business areas</li>
                    <li>A blue info banner indicates when the preference filter is active</li>
                    <li>You can override by selecting different business areas or viewing all items</li>
                    <li>Items assigned to you always appear regardless of business area</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
                    <p class="mb-0">Setting preferred business areas helps you focus on relevant items without manually filtering each time you visit RAID pages.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="business-areas">Business areas</h2>
                
                <p>Business areas are used to classify RAID items by organisational unit. Business areas are dynamically loaded from FIPS CMS.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data source:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Source:</strong> FIPS CMS category values with category_type = "Business area"</li>
                    <li><strong>Caching:</strong> Business areas are cached for 1 hour to improve performance</li>
                    <li><strong>Management:</strong> Business areas are managed in FIPS CMS Admin, not in COMPASS</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">To modify business areas:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Log in to FIPS CMS Admin</li>
                    <li>Navigate to Category Values</li>
                    <li>Create or edit entries with Category Type = "Business area"</li>
                    <li>Set appropriate sort order for display ordering</li>
                    <li>Changes appear in COMPASS within 1 hour (or after application restart)</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="metrics">Metric management</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Operational reports</h3>
                <p>Define metrics that products can report against.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Creating performance metrics:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Operational reports</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new metric"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter metric details:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Metric name</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> What the metric measures</li>
                            <li><strong>Unit:</strong> Unit of measurement (e.g., %, count, seconds, percentage)</li>
                            <li><strong>Target value:</strong> Optional default target</li>
                            <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> How often it should be reported (monthly, quarterly, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> Whether the metric is currently in use</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics</h3>
                <p>Define enterprise-level KPIs tracked across the organisation.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Creating enterprise metrics:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Enterprise metrics</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new metric"</strong></li>
                    <li>Configure the metric similar to performance metrics</li>
                    <li>Optionally link to strategic objectives</li>
                    <li>Save the metric</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="standards">Functional standards</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Standards management</h3>
                <p>Administrators can manage the DDaT functional standards framework.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Key tasks:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>View all functional standards</li>
                    <li>Create and edit standards</li>
                    <li>Manage themes within standards</li>
                    <li>Define practice areas within themes</li>
                    <li>Create and edit criteria within practice areas</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Standards hierarchy:</h4>
                <pre class="bg-light p-3">
Functional Standard
  └── Theme
      └── Practice Area
          └── Criterion
</pre>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Managing standards:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Functional standards</strong></li>
                    <li>Browse existing standards and their structure</li>
                    <li>Use <strong>"Create"</strong> buttons to add new elements at any level</li>
                    <li>Use <strong>"Edit"</strong> to modify existing elements</li>
                    <li>Ensure each criterion has clear description and assessment guidance</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0">Standards data can be synchronised from the DfE Standards CMS to ensure alignment with the official framework.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="objectives">Strategic objectives</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Managing strategic objectives</h3>
                <p>Define organisational objectives that products and RAID items can align to.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Creating objectives:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Administration → Strategic objectives</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create new objective"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter objective details:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear, concise objective statement</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the objective</li>
                            <li><strong>Start date:</strong> When the objective period begins</li>
                            <li><strong>End date:</strong> When the objective period ends</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Current status (active, achieved, cancelled)</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Relative importance</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Using objectives:</h4>
                <p>Once created, objectives can be linked to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Products</li>
                    <li>Risks</li>
                    <li>Issues</li>
                    <li>Actions</li>
                    <li>Milestones</li>
                    <li>Operational reports</li>
                </ul>

                <p>This enables strategic alignment tracking and reporting.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="maintenance">System maintenance</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data quality</h3>
                <p>Regular maintenance tasks for administrators:</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Review and clean-up:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review orphaned RAID items not linked to products</li>
                    <li>Check for duplicate entries</li>
                    <li>Identify and close stale risks or issues</li>
                    <li>Archive completed actions older than retention period</li>
                    <li>Review and update user accounts</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Data integrity:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verify product synchronisation from FIPS CMS</li>
                    <li>Check for broken links to external systems</li>
                    <li>Validate metric submissions for completeness</li>
                    <li>Review assessment data quality</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Monitoring</h3>
                <p>System health monitoring tasks:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review system logs for errors</li>
                    <li>Monitor API integration status</li>
                    <li>Check database performance</li>
                    <li>Review user activity logs</li>
                    <li>Monitor authentication and authorisation</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Backups</h3>
                <p>Database backup procedures:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Automated daily backups to Azure Blob Storage</li>
                    <li>Weekly full backups retained for 3 months</li>
                    <li>Transaction log backups every 15 minutes</li>
                    <li>Test restore procedures quarterly</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Updates and upgrades</h3>
                <p>System update procedures:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review release notes for new features and fixes</li>
                    <li>Test updates in development environment</li>
                    <li>Schedule maintenance windows for production updates</li>
                    <li>Communicate planned downtime to users</li>
                    <li>Perform post-update validation</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Administrator best practices</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Only grant administrator role to users who need it</li>
                    <li>Review user list regularly and deactivate unused accounts</li>
                    <li>Document administrator role assignments</li>
                    <li>Maintain at least 2-3 active administrators</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Configuration management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Document all custom settings and their purpose</li>
                    <li>Test setting changes in development before production</li>
                    <li>Communicate setting changes to affected users</li>
                    <li>Keep lookup tables clean and relevant</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data governance:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Establish data quality standards</li>
                    <li>Provide guidance and training to users</li>
                    <li>Monitor data quality metrics</li>
                    <li>Regularly review and clean data</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Security:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review access logs regularly</li>
                    <li>Monitor for unusual activity</li>
                    <li>Keep system and dependencies updated</li>
                    <li>Follow DfE security policies</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-primary mt-4">
                    <h3 class="h6">Support</h3>
                    <p class="mb-2">For administrator support:</p>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Review other documentation sections for detailed feature information</li>
                        <li>Contact the COMPASS development team for technical issues</li>
                        <li>Report bugs or request features via the support portal</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

